frameDefinitions: This frame covers descriptions of an entire human body, viewed as a gestalt (as opposed to descriptions based on salient body parts).
The size of an Entity is assessed in terms of the Degree by which it deviates from the norm.
Some individual or group ceases to be able to sustain an Endeavor (a long-term activity involving economic interaction with the public, often a business venture).
An Entity has a particular scalar Attribute with a value exceeding a contextually-specified or generally-understood standard.
An event or state (here termed an Eventuality) or time-Period is described in terms of the Degree to which its duration diverges from a standard.
An Item changes its physical size.
frameExamples: After a <t>lengthy</t> discussion with the Foreign Minister, Mr. Qian Qichen, they met the Prime Minister.
The pile of leaves had <t>shrunk</t> by about half after the first haul.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the individual (or individuals) being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
The thing whose size is being considered.
The <fen>Endeavor</fen> is rendered unable to continue its regular operations.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Value</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Value</fen> for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.

A situation, action or event whose duration is being described.  The Eventuality occurs as the External Argument if the adjective is used predicatively, or as the modified noun if the adjective is used attributively: <fex name='Eventuality'>The lecture</fex> was <t>short</t>. We had a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Eventuality'>conversation</fex>.

Sometimes these adjectives describe simply a period of time, rather than an event or state.  The Period almost invariably occurs as the modified noun with an attributive adjective: We waited for only a <t>short</t> <fex name='Period'>time</fex>. Use of the drug over a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Period'>period</fex> can cause memory loss.
This role identifies the <fen>Item</fen> whose size changes.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the expansion occurs.
listRoleExamples: Her campaign failed <fex>in 2008</fex> but found much more support in 2012.
The hot dog stand <fex>on 4th avenue</fex> flopped.
<fex>Joan's new sweater</fex> shrank to a size that might fit a doll.
